          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Class</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Unclass</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>STIGRef</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8 Security Technical Implementation Guide :: Version 2, Release: 6 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>TargetKey</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>aaf3e142-eed5-4506-b452-44454582801b</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>CCI_REF</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>CCI-000366</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STATUS>Open</STATUS>
        <FINDING_DETAILS>#echo '***XYLOK ICS***'
sysctl -a 2&gt;/dev/null | grep 'net.ipv6.conf.all.disable_ipv6'
echo '***XYLOK ICS***'
sysctl net.ipv6.conf.default.accept_redirects
echo '***XYLOK ICS***'
grep -Er '^[[:space:]]*net.ipv6.conf.default.accept_redirects' /run/sysctl.d/*.conf /usr/local/lib/sysctl.d/*.conf /usr/lib/sysctl.d/*.conf /lib/sysctl.d/*.conf /etc/sysctl.conf /etc/sysctl.d/*.conf 2&gt;/dev/null

Checking if IPv6 is disabled on the system:
🔍 IPv6 is not disabled

Checking the 'net.ipv6.conf.default.accept_redirects' setting using 'sysctl':
❌ net.ipv6.conf.default.accept_redirects = 1

Checking for the 'net.ipv6.conf.default.accept_redirects' setting in configuration files:
❌ No configuration files were found with the 'net.ipv6.conf.default.accept_redirects' setting


Xylok post-processing completed with no errors.
</FINDING_DETAILS>
        <COMMENTS>The 'net.ipv6.conf.default.accept_redirects' setting returned from 'sysctl' is set to '1', but should have returned '0'.
No configuration files were found with the 'net.ipv6.conf.default.accept_redirects' setting.</COMMENTS>
        <SEVERITY_OVERRIDE/>
        <SEVERITY_JUSTIFICATION/>
