        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Check_Content</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Verify that a separate file system/partition has been created for the system audit data path with the following command:

Note: /var/log/audit is used as the example as it is a common location.

$ sudo grep /var/log/audit /etc/fstab

UUID=3645951a /var/log/audit xfs defaults 1 2

If an entry for "/var/log/audit" does not exist, ask the System Administrator if the system audit logs are being written to a different file system/partition on the system, then grep for that file system/partition.

If a separate file system/partition does not exist for the system audit data path, this is a finding.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
