          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>CCI-000140</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STATUS>Open</STATUS>
        <FINDING_DETAILS>#echo '***XYLOK ICS***'
grep disk_full_action /etc/audit/auditd.conf

Checking that the OS takes the appropriate action when the audit storage volume is full:
❌ disk_full_action = SUSPEND


