          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Configure the audit system to generate an audit event for any successful/unsuccessful modifications to the "faillock" file by adding or updating the following rules in the "/etc/audit/rules.d/audit.rules" file:

-w /var/log/faillock -p wa -k logins

The audit daemon must be restarted for the changes to take effect.</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
