        <FINDING_DETAILS>#echo "***XYLOK ICS***"
pwck -r
echo "***XYLOK ICS***"
FILENAME="/etc/passwd"
echo "Interactive Users:"
while IFS=: read -r username password userid groupid comment homedir cmdshell
do
         if [[ "$cmdshell" != "/sbin/nologin" &amp;&amp; "$cmdshell" != "/sbin/halt" &amp;&amp; "$cmdshell" != "/bin/sync" &amp;&amp; "$cmdshell" != "/sbin/shutdown" &amp;&amp; "$cmdshell" != "/bin/false" &amp;&amp; "$cmdshell" != "/bin/true" &amp;&amp; "$cmdshell" != "/usr/sbin/nologin" ]]; then
                 echo "USER: $username"; stat -c "%a %n" $homedir
         fi
done &lt; $FILENAME

Checking that local interactive users have valid home directory assigned in '/etc/passwd':
✅ The home directory ('/root') for user ('root') exists and is valid.
✅ The home directory ('/home/deckerr') for user ('deckerr') exists and is valid.


Xylok post-processing completed with no errors.
</FINDING_DETAILS>
