          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>M</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Weight</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>10.0</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>Class</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Unclass</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>STIGRef</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>Red Hat Enterprise Linux 8 Security Technical Implementation Guide :: Version 2, Release: 6 Benchmark Date: 05 Jan 2026</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>TargetKey</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>aaf3e142-eed5-4506-b452-44454582801b</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STIG_DATA>
          <VULN_ATTRIBUTE>CCI_REF</VULN_ATTRIBUTE>
          <ATTRIBUTE_DATA>CCI-001764</ATTRIBUTE_DATA>
        </STIG_DATA>
        <STATUS>Open</STATUS>
        <FINDING_DETAILS>#echo '***XYLOK ICS***'
mount | grep /tmp
echo '***XYLOK ICS***'
cat /etc/fstab | grep /tmp

Checking if '/tmp' is mounted with 'nosuid' option:
❌ '/tmp' is not mounted on the system.


Checking that the 'nosuid' is configured for '/tmp':
❌ '/tmp' is not configured in '/etc/fstab'.


Xylok post-processing completed with no errors.
</FINDING_DETAILS>
        <COMMENTS>'/tmp' is not mounted on the system.
'/tmp' is not configured in '/etc/fstab'.</COMMENTS>
